# migrated from tests/cases/calibrate.it.chat (hermetic + isolated, perf-held)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test calibrate.it]
!timeout 0
# gen142 (E8): metacognitive calibration in Italian — the SAME behaviour through
# the SAME code path. Italian function words (è/un/una/non/ogni/supponi che) are
# canonicalized so the assertions and the supposition reach the English-parsing
# core; the follow-up cues ("perché lo pensi", "cosa ti farebbe cambiare idea")
# match the raw text. The reasoning verbalization stays in the core language, as
# every other .it ratchet does — the competence is the epistemic-state machinery,
# not a second phrasebook.

# INFERRED
> socrates è un uomo
< Learned: uomo(socrates).
> ogni uomo è un mortale
< Learned rule: mortale(X) :- uomo(X).
> socrates è un mortale?
< Yes.
> perché lo pensi?
< I'm confident but it's derived, not given: mortale(socrates) because uomo(socrates). I concluded it by applying a rule, so it's only as sound as those premises.
> cosa ti farebbe cambiare idea?
< It hangs on one premise: if I learned that socrates is a uomo were false, I'd stop concluding socrates is a mortale.

# KNOWN
> rex è un cane
< Learned: cane(rex).
> rex è un cane?
< Yes.
> perché lo pensi?
< I'm certain: rex is a cane is a fact you stated directly, so I hold it as known, not inferred.

# CONFLICTED
> alice è una persona
< Learned: persona(alice).
> alice non è una persona
< Learned: not persona(alice).
> alice è una persona?
< No.
> perché lo pensi?
< I'm genuinely unsure — I hold conflicting claims about alice: you told me it is a persona and also that it is not. Until that's resolved I can't commit either way.

# HYPOTHETICAL
> supponi che tweety è un uccello
< All right — assuming tweety is a uccello. Anything I conclude from it will be conditional on that.
> tweety è un uccello?
< Yes.
> cosa ti farebbe cambiare idea?
< Dropping the assumption — I only conclude tweety is a uccello because I'm supposing tweety is a uccello. Withdraw that and the conclusion goes with it.

